Uses of Package
org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp

  • Packages that use org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp 
    Package Description
    org.apache.freemarker.servlet
    Servlet for legacy "Model 2" frameworks that allows using FreeMarker templates instead of JSP as the MVC View (see in the Manual), also custom JSP tag support.
    org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp
    Allows JSP custom tags to be used inside FreeMarker templates as if they where FreeMarker directives.
    org.apache.freemarker.spring.web.view
    Spring Framework MVC View Support
  • Classes in org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp used by org.apache.freemarker.servlet 
    Class and Description
    TaglibFactory
    A hash model associated with a servlet context that can load JSP tag libraries associated with that servlet context.
    TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource
    A location within which we will look for META-INF/**/*.tld-s.
  • Classes in org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp used by org.apache.freemarker.servlet.jsp 
    Class and Description
    TaglibFactory
    A hash model associated with a servlet context that can load JSP tag libraries associated with that servlet context.
    TaglibFactory.Builder
    Creates a new TaglibFactory.
    TaglibFactory.ClearMetaInfTldSource
    When it occurs in the TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource list (TaglibFactory.getMetaInfTldSources()), all TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource-s before it will be disabled.
    TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource
    A location within which we will look for META-INF/**/*.tld-s.
    TaglibFactory.WebInfPerLibJarMetaInfTldSource
    To search TLD-s under sevletContext:/WEB-INF/lib/*.{jar,zip}/META-INF/**/*.tld, as requested by the JSP specification.
